37/* Unified iterator object.
38 *
39 * The goal of this template is to make the same iterator interface
40 * available to all types, and make it very easy and compact to use.
41 * hb_iter_tator objects are small, light-weight, objects that can be
42 * copied by value. If the collection / object being iterated on
43 * is writable, then the iterator returns lvalues, otherwise it
44 * returns rvalues.
45 *
46 * If iterator implementation implements operator!=, then it can be
47 * used in range-based for loop. That already happens if the iterator
48 * is random-access. Otherwise, the range-based for loop incurs
49 * one traversal to find end(), which can be avoided if written
50 * as a while-style for loop, or if iterator implements a faster
51 * __end__() method. */
52
53/*
54 * Base classes for iterators.
55 */
56
57/* Base class for all iterators. */
58template <typename iter_t, typename Item = typename iter_t::__item_t__>
59struct hb_iter_t
60{
61 typedef Item item_t;
62 constexpr unsigned get_item_size () const { return hb_static_size (Item); }
63 static constexpr bool is_iterator = true;
64 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator = false;
65 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = false;
66
67 private:
68 /* https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curiously_recurring_template_pattern */
69 const iter_t* thiz () const { return static_cast<const iter_t *> (this); }
70 iter_t* thiz () { return static_cast< iter_t *> (this); }
71 public:
72
73 /* Operators. */
74 iter_t iter () const { return *thiz(); }
75 iter_t operator + () const { return *thiz(); }
76 iter_t _begin () const { return *thiz(); }
77 iter_t begin () const { return _begin (); }
78 iter_t _end () const { return thiz()->__end__ (); }
79 iter_t end () const { return _end (); }
80 explicit operator bool () const { return thiz()->__more__ (); }
81 unsigned len () const { return thiz()->__len__ (); }
82 /* The following can only be enabled if item_t is reference type. Otherwise
83 * it will be returning pointer to temporary rvalue. */
84 template <typename T = item_t,
85 hb_enable_if (std::is_reference<T>::value)>
86 hb_remove_reference<item_t>* operator -> () const { return std::addressof (**thiz()); }
87 item_t operator * () const { return thiz()->__item__ (); }
88 item_t operator * () { return thiz()->__item__ (); }
89 item_t operator [] (unsigned i) const { return thiz()->__item_at__ (i); }
90 item_t operator [] (unsigned i) { return thiz()->__item_at__ (i); }
91 iter_t& operator += (unsigned count) & { thiz()->__forward__ (count); return *thiz(); }
92 iter_t operator += (unsigned count) && { thiz()->__forward__ (count); return *thiz(); }
93 iter_t& operator ++ () & { thiz()->__next__ (); return *thiz(); }
94 iter_t operator ++ () && { thiz()->__next__ (); return *thiz(); }
95 iter_t& operator -= (unsigned count) & { thiz()->__rewind__ (count); return *thiz(); }
96 iter_t operator -= (unsigned count) && { thiz()->__rewind__ (count); return *thiz(); }
97 iter_t& operator -- () & { thiz()->__prev__ (); return *thiz(); }
98 iter_t operator -- () && { thiz()->__prev__ (); return *thiz(); }
99 iter_t operator + (unsigned count) const { auto c = thiz()->iter (); c += count; return c; }
100 friend iter_t operator + (unsigned count, const iter_t &it) { return it + count; }
101 iter_t operator ++ (int) { iter_t c (*thiz()); ++*thiz(); return c; }
102 iter_t operator - (unsigned count) const { auto c = thiz()->iter (); c -= count; return c; }
103 iter_t operator -- (int) { iter_t c (*thiz()); --*thiz(); return c; }
104 template <typename T>
105 iter_t& operator >> (T &v) & { v = **thiz(); ++*thiz(); return *thiz(); }
106 template <typename T>
107 iter_t operator >> (T &v) && { v = **thiz(); ++*thiz(); return *thiz(); }
108 template <typename T>
109 iter_t& operator << (const T v) & { **thiz() = v; ++*thiz(); return *thiz(); }
110 template <typename T>
111 iter_t operator << (const T v) && { **thiz() = v; ++*thiz(); return *thiz(); }
112
113 protected:
114 hb_iter_t () = default;
115 hb_iter_t (const hb_iter_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
116 hb_iter_t (hb_iter_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
117 hb_iter_t& operator = (const hb_iter_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
118 hb_iter_t& operator = (hb_iter_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
119};
120

122 using item_t = typename Name::item_t; \
123 using Name::_begin; \
124 using Name::begin; \
125 using Name::_end; \
126 using Name::end; \
127 using Name::get_item_size; \
128 using Name::is_iterator; \
129 using Name::iter; \
130 using Name::operator bool; \
131 using Name::len; \
132 using Name::operator ->; \
133 using Name::operator *; \
134 using Name::operator []; \
135 using Name::operator +=; \
136 using Name::operator ++; \
137 using Name::operator -=; \
138 using Name::operator --; \
139 using Name::operator +; \
140 using Name::operator -; \
141 using Name::operator >>; \
142 using Name::operator <<; \
143 static_assert (true, "")

145/* Returns iterator / item type of a type. */
146template <typename Iterable>
147using hb_iter_type = decltype (hb_deref (hb_declval (Iterable)).iter ());
148template <typename Iterable>
149using hb_item_type = decltype (*hb_deref (hb_declval (Iterable)).iter ());
150

152template <typename> struct hb_array_t;
153template <typename> struct hb_sorted_array_t;
154
155struct
156{
157 template <typename T> hb_iter_type<T>
158 operator () (T&& c) const
159 { return hb_deref (std::forward<T> (c)).iter (); }
160
161 /* Specialization for C arrays. */
162
163 template <typename Type> inline hb_array_t<Type>
164 operator () (Type *array, unsigned int length) const
165 { return hb_array_t<Type> (array, length); }
166
167 template <typename Type, unsigned int length> hb_array_t<Type>
168 operator () (Type (&array)[length]) const
169 { return hb_array_t<Type> (array, length); }
170
171}

174{

176 impl (T&& c, hb_priority<1>) const HB_RETURN (unsigned, c.len ())

185}

188/* Mixin to fill in what the subclass doesn't provide. */
189template <typename iter_t, typename item_t = typename iter_t::__item_t__>
190struct hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t
191{
192 private:
193 /* https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curiously_recurring_template_pattern */
194 const iter_t* thiz () const { return static_cast<const iter_t *> (this); }
195 iter_t* thiz () { return static_cast< iter_t *> (this); }
196 public:
197
198 /* Access: Implement __item__(), or __item_at__() if random-access. */
199 item_t __item__ () const { return (*thiz())[0]; }
200 item_t __item_at__ (unsigned i) const { return *(*thiz() + i); }
201
202 /* Termination: Implement __more__(), or __len__() if random-access. */
203 bool __more__ () const { return bool (thiz()->len ()); }
204 unsigned __len__ () const
205 { iter_t c (*thiz()); unsigned l = 0; while (c) { c++; l++; } return l; }
206
207 /* Advancing: Implement __next__(), or __forward__() if random-access. */
208 void __next__ () { *thiz() += 1; }
209 void __forward__ (unsigned n) { while (*thiz() && n--) ++*thiz(); }
210
211 /* Rewinding: Implement __prev__() or __rewind__() if bidirectional. */
212 void __prev__ () { *thiz() -= 1; }
213 void __rewind__ (unsigned n) { while (*thiz() && n--) --*thiz(); }
214
215 /* Range-based for: Implement __end__() if can be done faster,
216 * and operator!=. */
217 iter_t __end__ () const
218 {
219 if (thiz()->is_random_access_iterator)
220 return *thiz() + thiz()->len ();
221 /* Above expression loops twice. Following loops once. */
222 auto it = *thiz();
223 while (it) ++it;
224 return it;
225 }
226
227 protected:
228 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t () = default;
229 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t (const hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
230 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t (hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
231 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t& operator = (const hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
232 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t& operator = (hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
233};
234
235template <typename iter_t, typename item_t = typename iter_t::__item_t__>
236struct hb_iter_with_fallback_t :
237 hb_iter_t<iter_t, item_t>,
238 hb_iter_fallback_mixin_t<iter_t, item_t>
239{
240 protected:
241 hb_iter_with_fallback_t () = default;
242 hb_iter_with_fallback_t (const hb_iter_with_fallback_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
243 hb_iter_with_fallback_t (hb_iter_with_fallback_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
244 hb_iter_with_fallback_t& operator = (const hb_iter_with_fallback_t &o HB_UNUSED) = default;
245 hb_iter_with_fallback_t& operator = (hb_iter_with_fallback_t &&o HB_UNUSED) = default;
246};

252/* hb_is_iterator() / hb_is_iterator_of() */
253
254template<typename Iter, typename Item>
255struct hb_is_iterator_of
256{
257 template <typename Item2 = Item>
258 static hb_true_type impl (hb_priority<2>, hb_iter_t<Iter, hb_type_identity<Item2>> *);
259 static hb_false_type impl (hb_priority<0>, const void *);
260
261 public:
262 static constexpr bool value = decltype (impl (hb_prioritize, hb_declval (Iter*)))::value;
263};
264#define hb_is_iterator_of(Iter, Item) hb_is_iterator_of<Iter, Item>::value
265#define hb_is_iterator(Iter) hb_is_iterator_of (Iter, typename Iter::item_t)
266#define hb_is_sorted_iterator_of(Iter, Item) (hb_is_iterator_of<Iter, Item>::value && Iter::is_sorted_iterator)
267#define hb_is_sorted_iterator(Iter) hb_is_sorted_iterator_of (Iter, typename Iter::item_t)
268
269/* hb_is_iterable() */
270
271template <typename T>
272struct hb_is_iterable
273{
274 private:
275
276 template <typename U>
277 static auto impl (hb_priority<1>) -> decltype (hb_declval (U).iter (), hb_true_type ());
278
279 template <typename>
280 static hb_false_type impl (hb_priority<0>);
281
282 public:
283 static constexpr bool value = decltype (impl<T> (hb_prioritize))::value;
284};
285#define hb_is_iterable(Iterable) hb_is_iterable<Iterable>::value

287/* hb_is_source_of() / hb_is_sink_of() */
288
289template<typename Iter, typename Item>
290struct hb_is_source_of
291{
292 private:
293 template <typename Iter2 = Iter,
294 hb_enable_if (hb_is_convertible (typename Iter2::item_t, hb_add_lvalue_reference<const Item>))>
295 static hb_true_type impl (hb_priority<2>);
296 template <typename Iter2 = Iter>
297 static auto impl (hb_priority<1>) -> decltype (hb_declval (Iter2) >> hb_declval (Item &), hb_true_type ());
298 static hb_false_type impl (hb_priority<0>);
299
300 public:
301 static constexpr bool value = decltype (impl (hb_prioritize))::value;
302};
303#define hb_is_source_of(Iter, Item) hb_is_source_of<Iter, Item>::value
304
305template<typename Iter, typename Item>
306struct hb_is_sink_of
307{
308 private:
309 template <typename Iter2 = Iter,
310 hb_enable_if (hb_is_convertible (typename Iter2::item_t, hb_add_lvalue_reference<Item>))>
311 static hb_true_type impl (hb_priority<2>);
312 template <typename Iter2 = Iter>
313 static auto impl (hb_priority<1>) -> decltype (hb_declval (Iter2) << hb_declval (Item), hb_true_type ());
314 static hb_false_type impl (hb_priority<0>);
315
316 public:
317 static constexpr bool value = decltype (impl (hb_prioritize))::value;
318};
319#define hb_is_sink_of(Iter, Item) hb_is_sink_of<Iter, Item>::value
320
321/* This is commonly used, so define: */
322#define hb_is_sorted_source_of(Iter, Item) \
323 (hb_is_source_of(Iter, Item) && Iter::is_sorted_iterator)

360/* hb_map(), hb_filter(), hb_reduce() */
361
362enum class hb_function_sortedness_t {
363 NOT_SORTED,
364 RETAINS_SORTING,
365 SORTED,
366};
367
368template <typename Iter, typename Proj, hb_function_sortedness_t Sorted,
369 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iter))>
370struct hb_map_iter_t :
371 hb_iter_t<hb_map_iter_t<Iter, Proj, Sorted>,
372 decltype (hb_get (hb_declval (Proj), *hb_declval (Iter)))>
373{
374 hb_map_iter_t (const Iter& it, Proj f_) : it (it), f (f_) {}
375
376 typedef decltype (hb_get (hb_declval (Proj), *hb_declval (Iter))) __item_t__;
377 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator = Iter::is_random_access_iterator;
378 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator =
379 Sorted == hb_function_sortedness_t::SORTED ? true :
380 Sorted == hb_function_sortedness_t::RETAINS_SORTING ? Iter::is_sorted_iterator :
381 false;
382 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return hb_get (f.get (), *it); }
383 __item_t__ __item_at__ (unsigned i) const { return hb_get (f.get (), it[i]); }
384 bool __more__ () const { return bool (it); }
385 unsigned __len__ () const { return it.len (); }
386 void __next__ () { ++it; }
387 void __forward__ (unsigned n) { it += n; }
388 void __prev__ () { --it; }
389 void __rewind__ (unsigned n) { it -= n; }
390 hb_map_iter_t __end__ () const { return hb_map_iter_t (it._end (), f); }
391 bool operator != (const hb_map_iter_t& o) const
392 { return it != o.it; }
393
394 private:
395 Iter it;
396 hb_reference_wrapper<Proj> f;
397};
398
399template <typename Proj, hb_function_sortedness_t Sorted>
400struct hb_map_iter_factory_t
401{
402 hb_map_iter_factory_t (Proj f) : f (f) {}
403
404 template <typename Iter,
405 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iter))>
406 hb_map_iter_t<Iter, Proj, Sorted>
407 operator () (Iter it)
408 { return hb_map_iter_t<Iter, Proj, Sorted> (it, f); }
409
410 private:
411 Proj f;
412};
413struct
414{
415 template <typename Proj>
416 hb_map_iter_factory_t<Proj, hb_function_sortedness_t::NOT_SORTED>
417 operator () (Proj&& f) const
418 { return hb_map_iter_factory_t<Proj, hb_function_sortedness_t::NOT_SORTED> (f); }
419}
420HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_map);
421struct
422{
423 template <typename Proj>

427}
428HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_map_retains_sorting);
429struct
430{

435}
436HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_map_sorted);

438template <typename Iter, typename Pred, typename Proj,
439 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iter))>
440struct hb_filter_iter_t :
441 hb_iter_with_fallback_t<hb_filter_iter_t<Iter, Pred, Proj>,
442 typename Iter::item_t>
443{
444 hb_filter_iter_t (const Iter& it_, Pred p_, Proj f_) : it (it_), p (p_), f (f_)
445 { while (it && !hb_has (p.get (), hb_get (f.get (), *it))) ++it; }
446
447 typedef typename Iter::item_t __item_t__;
448 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = Iter::is_sorted_iterator;
449 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return *it; }
450 bool __more__ () const { return bool (it); }
451 void __next__ () { do ++it; while (it && !hb_has (p.get (), hb_get (f.get (), *it))); }
452 void __prev__ () { do --it; while (it && !hb_has (p.get (), hb_get (f.get (), *it))); }
453 hb_filter_iter_t __end__ () const { return hb_filter_iter_t (it._end (), p, f); }
454 bool operator != (const hb_filter_iter_t& o) const
455 { return it != o.it; }
456
457 private:
458 Iter it;
459 hb_reference_wrapper<Pred> p;
460 hb_reference_wrapper<Proj> f;
461};
462template <typename Pred, typename Proj>
463struct hb_filter_iter_factory_t
464{
465 hb_filter_iter_factory_t (Pred p, Proj f) : p (p), f (f) {}
466
467 template <typename Iter,
468 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iter))>
469 hb_filter_iter_t<Iter, Pred, Proj>
470 operator () (Iter it)
471 { return hb_filter_iter_t<Iter, Pred, Proj> (it, p, f); }
472
473 private:
474 Pred p;
475 Proj f;
476};
477struct
478{
479 template <typename Pred = decltype ((hb_identity)),
480 typename Proj = decltype ((hb_identity))>
481 hb_filter_iter_factory_t<Pred, Proj>
482 operator () (Pred&& p = hb_identity, Proj&& f = hb_identity) const
483 { return hb_filter_iter_factory_t<Pred, Proj> (p, f); }
484}
485HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_filter);

487template <typename Redu, typename InitT>
488struct hb_reduce_t
489{
490 hb_reduce_t (Redu r, InitT init_value) : r (r), init_value (init_value) {}
491
492 template <typename Iter,
493 hb_requires (hb_is_iterator (Iter)),
494 typename AccuT = hb_decay<decltype (hb_declval (Redu) (hb_declval (InitT), hb_declval (typename Iter::item_t)))>>
495 AccuT
496 operator () (Iter it)
497 {
498 AccuT value = init_value;
499 for (; it; ++it)
500 value = r (value, *it);
501 return value;
502 }
503
504 private:
505 Redu r;
506 InitT init_value;
507};
508struct
509{
510 template <typename Redu, typename InitT>
511 hb_reduce_t<Redu, InitT>
512 operator () (Redu&& r, InitT init_value) const
513 { return hb_reduce_t<Redu, InitT> (r, init_value); }
514}
515HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_reduce);

518/* hb_zip() */
519
520template <typename A, typename B>
521struct hb_zip_iter_t :
522 hb_iter_t<hb_zip_iter_t<A, B>,
523 hb_pair_t<typename A::item_t, typename B::item_t>>
524{
525 hb_zip_iter_t () {}
526 hb_zip_iter_t (const A& a, const B& b) : a (a), b (b) {}
527
528 typedef hb_pair_t<typename A::item_t, typename B::item_t> __item_t__;
529 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator =
530 A::is_random_access_iterator &&
531 B::is_random_access_iterator;
532 /* Note. The following categorization is only valid if A is strictly sorted,
533 * ie. does NOT have duplicates. Previously I tried to categorize sortedness
534 * more granularly, see commits:
535 *
536 * 513762849a683914fc266a17ddf38f133cccf072
537 * 4d3cf2adb669c345cc43832d11689271995e160a
538 *
539 * However, that was not enough, since hb_sorted_array_t, hb_sorted_vector_t,
540 * SortedArrayOf, etc all needed to be updated to add more variants. At that
541 * point I saw it not worth the effort, and instead we now deem all sorted
542 * collections as essentially strictly-sorted for the purposes of zip.
543 *
544 * The above assumption is not as bad as it sounds. Our "sorted" comes with
545 * no guarantees. It's just a contract, put in place to help you remember,
546 * and think about, whether an iterator you receive is expected to be
547 * sorted or not. As such, it's not perfect by definition, and should not
548 * be treated so. The inaccuracy here just errs in the direction of being
549 * more permissive, so your code compiles instead of erring on the side of
550 * marking your zipped iterator unsorted in which case your code won't
551 * compile.
552 *
553 * This semantical limitation does NOT affect logic in any other place I
554 * know of as of this writing.
555 */
556 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = A::is_sorted_iterator;
557
558 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return __item_t__ (*a, *b); }
559 __item_t__ __item_at__ (unsigned i) const { return __item_t__ (a[i], b[i]); }
560 bool __more__ () const { return bool (a) && bool (b); }
561 unsigned __len__ () const { return hb_min (a.len (), b.len ()); }
562 void __next__ () { ++a; ++b; }
563 void __forward__ (unsigned n) { a += n; b += n; }
564 void __prev__ () { --a; --b; }
565 void __rewind__ (unsigned n) { a -= n; b -= n; }
566 hb_zip_iter_t __end__ () const { return hb_zip_iter_t (a._end (), b._end ()); }
567 /* Note, we should stop if ANY of the iters reaches end. As such two compare
568 * unequal if both items are unequal, NOT if either is unequal. */
569 bool operator != (const hb_zip_iter_t& o) const
570 { return a != o.a && b != o.b; }
571
572 private:
573 A a;
574 B b;
575};
576struct
577{ HB_PARTIALIZE(2);
578 template <typename A, typename B,
579 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (A) && hb_is_iterable (B))>
580 hb_zip_iter_t<hb_iter_type<A>, hb_iter_type<B>>
581 operator () (A&& a, B&& b) const
582 { return hb_zip_iter_t<hb_iter_type<A>, hb_iter_type<B>> (hb_iter (a), hb_iter (b)); }
583}
584HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_zip);

586/* hb_concat() */
587
588template <typename A, typename B>
589struct hb_concat_iter_t :
590 hb_iter_t<hb_concat_iter_t<A, B>, typename A::item_t>
591{
592 hb_concat_iter_t () {}
593 hb_concat_iter_t (A& a, B& b) : a (a), b (b) {}
594 hb_concat_iter_t (const A& a, const B& b) : a (a), b (b) {}
595
596
597 typedef typename A::item_t __item_t__;
598 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator =
599 A::is_random_access_iterator &&
600 B::is_random_access_iterator;
601 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = false;
602
603 __item_t__ __item__ () const
604 {
605 if (!a)
606 return *b;
607 return *a;
608 }
609
610 __item_t__ __item_at__ (unsigned i) const
611 {
612 unsigned a_len = a.len ();
613 if (i < a_len)
614 return a[i];
615 return b[i - a_len];
616 }
617
618 bool __more__ () const { return bool (a) || bool (b); }
619
620 unsigned __len__ () const { return a.len () + b.len (); }
621
622 void __next__ ()
623 {
624 if (a)
625 ++a;
626 else
627 ++b;
628 }
629
630 void __forward__ (unsigned n)
631 {
632 if (!n) return;
633 if (!is_random_access_iterator) {
634 while (n-- && *this) {
635 (*this)++;
636 }
637 return;
638 }
639
640 unsigned a_len = a.len ();
641 if (n > a_len) {
642 n -= a_len;
643 a.__forward__ (a_len);
644 b.__forward__ (n);
645 } else {
646 a.__forward__ (n);
647 }
648 }
649
650 hb_concat_iter_t __end__ () const { return hb_concat_iter_t (a._end (), b._end ()); }
651 bool operator != (const hb_concat_iter_t& o) const
652 {
653 return a != o.a
654 || b != o.b;
655 }
656
657 private:
658 A a;
659 B b;
660};
661struct
662{ HB_PARTIALIZE(2);
663 template <typename A, typename B,
664 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (A) && hb_is_iterable (B))>
665 hb_concat_iter_t<hb_iter_type<A>, hb_iter_type<B>>
666 operator () (A&& a, B&& b) const
667 { return hb_concat_iter_t<hb_iter_type<A>, hb_iter_type<B>> (hb_iter (a), hb_iter (b)); }
668}
669HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_concat);

701/* hb_range()/hb_iota()/hb_repeat() */

703template <typename T, typename S>
704struct hb_range_iter_t :
705 hb_iter_t<hb_range_iter_t<T, S>, T>
706{
707 hb_range_iter_t (T start, T end_, S step) : v (start), end_ (end_for (start, end_, step)), step (step) {}
708
709 typedef T __item_t__;
710 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator = true;
711 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = true;
712 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return hb_ridentity (v); }
713 __item_t__ __item_at__ (unsigned j) const { return v + j * step; }
714 bool __more__ () const { return v != end_; }
715 unsigned __len__ () const { return !step ? UINT_MAX : (end_ - v) / step; }
716 void __next__ () { v += step; }
717 void __forward__ (unsigned n) { v += n * step; }
718 void __prev__ () { v -= step; }
719 void __rewind__ (unsigned n) { v -= n * step; }
720 hb_range_iter_t __end__ () const { return hb_range_iter_t (end_, end_, step); }
721 bool operator != (const hb_range_iter_t& o) const
722 { return v != o.v; }
723
724 private:
725 static inline T end_for (T start, T end_, S step)
726 {
727 if (!step)
728 return end_;
729 auto res = (end_ - start) % step;
730 if (!res)
731 return end_;
732 end_ += step - res;
733 return end_;
734 }
735
736 private:
737 T v;
738 T end_;
739 S step;
740};
741struct
742{
743 template <typename T = unsigned> hb_range_iter_t<T, unsigned>
744 operator () (T end = (unsigned) -1) const
745 { return hb_range_iter_t<T, unsigned> (0, end, 1u); }
746
747 template <typename T, typename S = unsigned> hb_range_iter_t<T, S>
748 operator () (T start, T end, S step = 1u) const
749 { return hb_range_iter_t<T, S> (start, end, step); }
750}
751HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_range);

753template <typename T, typename S>
754struct hb_iota_iter_t :
755 hb_iter_with_fallback_t<hb_iota_iter_t<T, S>, T>
756{
757 hb_iota_iter_t (T start, S step) : v (start), step (step) {}
758
759 private:
760
761 template <typename S2 = S>
762 auto
763 inc (hb_type_identity<S2> s, hb_priority<1>)
764 -> hb_void_t<decltype (hb_invoke (std::forward<S2> (s), hb_declval<T&> ()))>
765 { v = hb_invoke (std::forward<S2> (s), v); }
766
767 void
768 inc (S s, hb_priority<0>)
769 { v += s; }
770
771 public:
772
773 typedef T __item_t__;
774 static constexpr bool is_random_access_iterator = true;
775 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = true;
776 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return hb_ridentity (v); }
777 bool __more__ () const { return true; }
778 unsigned __len__ () const { return UINT_MAX; }
779 void __next__ () { inc (step, hb_prioritize); }
780 void __prev__ () { v -= step; }
781 hb_iota_iter_t __end__ () const { return *this; }
782 bool operator != (const hb_iota_iter_t& o) const { return true; }
783
784 private:
785 T v;
786 S step;
787};
788struct
789{
790 template <typename T = unsigned, typename S = unsigned> hb_iota_iter_t<T, S>
791 operator () (T start = 0u, S step = 1u) const
792 { return hb_iota_iter_t<T, S> (start, step); }
793}
794HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_iota);

952
953struct
954{
955 template <typename Iterable,
956 typename Pred = decltype ((hb_identity)),
957 typename Proj = decltype ((hb_identity)),
958 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (Iterable))>
959 bool operator () (Iterable&& c,
960 Pred&& p = hb_identity,
961 Proj&& f = hb_identity) const
962 {
963 for (auto it = hb_iter (c); it; ++it)
964 if (!hb_match (std::forward<Pred> (p), hb_get (std::forward<Proj> (f), *it)))
965 return false;
966 return true;
967 }
968}
969HB_FUNCOBJ (hb_all);

977 Pred&& p = hb_identity,
978 Proj&& f = hb_identity) const
979 {
980 for (auto it = hb_iter (c); it; ++it)

982 return true;
